#: ../../../api/pool.rst:2
msgid "`!psycopg_pool` -- Connection pool implementations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:9
msgid ""
"A connection pool is an object used to create and maintain a limited amount "
"of PostgreSQL connections, reducing the time requested by the program to "
"obtain a working connection and allowing an arbitrary large number of "
"concurrent threads or tasks to use a controlled amount of resources on the "
"server. See :ref:`connection-pools` for more details and usage pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:15
msgid "This package exposes a few connection pool classes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:17
msgid ""
"`ConnectionPool` is a synchronous connection pool yielding `~psycopg."
"Connection` objects and can be used by multithread applications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:20
msgid ""
"`AsyncConnectionPool` has an interface similar to `!ConnectionPool`, but "
"with `asyncio` functions replacing blocking functions, and yields `~psycopg."
"AsyncConnection` instances."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:24
msgid ""
"`NullConnectionPool` is a `!ConnectionPool` subclass exposing the same "
"interface of its parent, but not keeping any unused connection in its state. "
"See :ref:`null-pool` for details about related use cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:28
msgid ""
"`AsyncNullConnectionPool` has the same behaviour of the `!"
"NullConnectionPool`, but with the same async interface of the `!"
"AsyncConnectionPool`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:32
msgid ""
"The `!psycopg_pool` package is distributed separately from the main "
"`psycopg` package: use ``pip install \"psycopg[pool]\"``, or ``pip install "
"psycopg_pool``, to make it available. See :ref:`pool-installation`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:36
msgid ""
"The version numbers indicated in this page refer to the `!psycopg_pool` "
"package, not to `psycopg`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:41
msgid "The `!ConnectionPool` class"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:45
msgid ""
"This class implements a connection pool serving `~psycopg.Connection` "
"instances (or subclasses). The constructor has *alot* of arguments, but only "
"`!conninfo` and `!min_size` are the fundamental ones, all the other "
"arguments have meaningful defaults and can probably be tweaked later, if "
"required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:51
msgid ""
"The connection string. See `~psycopg.Connection.connect()` for details. If "
"it is a callable it will be called at every connection attempt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:56
msgid ""
"The class of the connections to serve. It should be a `!Connection` subclass."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:60
msgid ""
"Extra arguments to pass to `!connect()`. Note that this is *one dict "
"argument* of the pool constructor, which is expanded as `connect()` keyword "
"parameters. If it is a callable it will be called at every connection "
"attempt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:66
msgid ""
"The minimum number of connection the pool will hold. The pool will actively "
"try to create new connections if some are lost (closed, broken) and will try "
"to never go below `!min_size`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:72
msgid ""
"The maximum number of connections the pool will hold. If `!None`, or equal "
"to `!min_size`, the pool will not grow or shrink. If larger than `!"
"min_size`, the pool can grow if more than `!min_size` connections are "
"requested at the same time and will shrink back after the extra connections "
"have been unused for more than `!max_idle` seconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:80
msgid ""
"If `!True`, open the pool, creating the required connections, on init. If `!"
"False`, open the pool when `!open()` is called or when the pool context is "
"entered. See the `open()` method documentation for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:86
msgid ""
"A callback to configure a connection after creation. Useful, for instance, "
"to configure its adapters. If the connection is used to run internal queries "
"(to inspect the database) make sure to close an eventual transaction before "
"leaving the function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:93
msgid ""
"A callback to check that a connection is working correctly when obtained by "
"the pool. The callback is called at every `getconn()` or `connection()`: the "
"connection is only passed to the client if the callback doesn't throw an "
"exception. By default no check is made on the connection. You can provide "
"the `check_connection()` pool static method if you want to perform a simple "
"check."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:102
msgid ""
"If `!True`, calling `~psycopg.Connection.close()` on the connection will not "
"actually close it, but it will return the connection to the pool, like in "
"`~ConnectionPool.putconn()`. Use it if you want to use Psycopg pool with "
"SQLAlchemy. See :ref:`pool-sqlalchemy`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:111
msgid ""
"A callback to reset a function after it has been returned to the pool. The "
"connection is guaranteed to be passed to the `!reset()` function in \"idle\" "
"state (no transaction). When leaving the `!reset()` function the connection "
"must be left in *idle* state, otherwise it is discarded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:118
msgid ""
"An optional name to give to the pool, useful, for instance, to identify it "
"in the logs if more than one pool is used. if not specified pick a "
"sequential name such as ``pool-1``, ``pool-2``, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:124
msgid ""
"The default maximum time in seconds that a client can wait to receive a "
"connection from the pool (using `connection()` or `getconn()`). Note that "
"these methods allow to override the `!timeout` default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:130
msgid ""
"Maximum number of requests that can be queued to the pool, after which new "
"requests will fail, raising `TooManyRequests`. 0 means no queue limit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:135
msgid ""
"The maximum lifetime of a connection in the pool, in seconds. Connections "
"used for longer get closed and replaced by a new one. The amount is reduced "
"by a random amount up to 5% to avoid mass eviction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:141
msgid ""
"Maximum time, in seconds, that a connection can stay unused in the pool "
"before being closed, and the pool shrunk. This only happens to connections "
"more than `!min_size`, if `!max_size` allowed the pool to grow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:147
msgid ""
"Maximum time, in seconds, the pool will try to create a connection. If a "
"connection attempt fails, the pool will try to reconnect a few times, using "
"an exponential backoff and some random factor to avoid mass attempts. If "
"repeated attempts fail, after `!reconnect_timeout` second the connection "
"attempt is aborted and the `!reconnect_failed()` callback invoked."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:157
msgid ""
"Callback invoked if an attempt to create a new connection fails for more "
"than `!reconnect_timeout` seconds. The user may decide, for instance, to "
"terminate the program (executing `sys.exit()`). By default don't do "
"anything: restart a new connection attempt (if the number of connection fell "
"below `!min_size`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:166
msgid ""
"Number of background worker threads used to maintain the pool state. "
"Background workers are used for example to create new connections and to "
"clean up connections when they are returned to the pool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:172
msgid "added `!open` parameter to the constructor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:175 ../../../api/pool.rst:325
msgid "added `!check` parameter to the constructor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:178
msgid ""
"the class is generic and `!connection_class` provides types type variable. "
"See :ref:`pool-generic`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:182 ../../../api/pool.rst:331
msgid "added `!close_returns` parameter to the constructor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:185
msgid "`conninfo` and `kwargs` can be callable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:190
msgid ""
"At the moment, the default value for the `!open` parameter is `!True`; In a "
"future version, the default will be changed to `!False`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:193
msgid ""
"If you expect the pool to be open on creation even if you don't use the pool "
"as context manager, you should specify the parameter `!open=True` explicitly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/pool.rst:197
msgid ""
"Starting from psycopg_pool 3.2, a warning is raised if the pool is used with "
"the expectation of being implicitly opened in the constructor and `!open` is "
"not specified."
msgstr ""

